review_blob: The foggy intense taste that is common from Butte Creek does not work with a pilsner.  Other beers are better.
pours with a slight white head and a gorgeous amber colour with a slight cloudiness.  Full bodied taste lots of hops. Aftertaste is pleasant as expected from an India Pale Ale.
beer_name: Butte Creek Organic India Pale Ale

review_blob: Rich yellow in color with a modest white head.  Nice aftertaste.  Head ramains throughout drink.
Pours a golden yellow with a modest head that remains till the end of the drink.  I would drink this beer again, especially if in Asia.
Nice rich brown color with yellow head.  Also smells rich and sweet.  Unfortunatey thats where the good points end.  Its far too sharp in the mouth and it tastes blandly bitter.
Pours golden color with minimal white head.  Rich smell.  A nice tasting easy to drink pilsner.
Poured pale yellow with a minimal white head that dissipated quickly.  No smell, bland taste.  Something to get drunk on but not enjoy.
pours yellow with a minimal white head.  Smells typical for a pilsner.  Tastes light, smooth and inoffensive but almost like a tonic water with the palate to match.  Aftertaste is slight but stale.

Similar to drinking cold, carbonated decaf coffee which despite how it sounds is surprisingly not bad. It has a definite coffee after taste .This beer is good to try if you like experimenting with your choices of beer. I would not buy this beer for myself, but if someone bought it for me I would drink it. Its more of a beer flavored coffee than a coffee flavored beer.
Gorgeous amber color with nice sized cream head.  Minimal smell.  Slightly bitter taste with a hint of spice, but almost sweet.  Great beer, will drink again.
Nice flavor.  It was a nice twist on a cola beverage.  I enjoyed drinking it.

Nice caramel head, though a little thin.  Very dark color.  An almost sweet, hint of chocolate taste.  Goes down smooth with tasty finish.  I served this beer to friends who do not like dark beers and they enjoyed it!
Smell is sour.  Taste is slightly rotten.  The only redeeming quality was the light bubbly palate.  This beer was a disappointment.  I could barely finish it, my friend dumped his out.
